examples.en: He owes me a large sum of money.
Let's go and see Joe  he owes me!
The thesis owes much to his adviser.
He owes a great deal to his publishers.
She owes thousands of dollars to creditors.
He probably owes his life to her prompt action.
The company owes him several months in back pay.
The $1 I owed him and the $1 he owes me cancel out.
She still owes me for all the times I've helped her out.
This new theory owes much to Einstein's Relativity Theory.
She owes her flexibility to her early training as a dancer.
Their success owes more to good luck than to careful management.
He owes allegiance to them for all the help they have given him.
The company owes its success to its excellent training programme.
He owes money to a list of people as long as your arm (=a very long list).
He owes his life to (=he is still alive because of) the prompt action of a neighbour.
